1
00:00:01,600 --> 00:00:05,880
ALL DEPICTED EVENTS ARE FICTIONAL

2
00:00:17,040 --> 00:00:21,120
I acknowledge your determination,
even though your plans are stupid.

3
00:00:21,200 --> 00:00:22,680
<i>Why is it so hard with Qin?</i>

4
00:00:22,760 --> 00:00:24,160
<i>What if you can't win him over?</i>

5
00:00:24,240 --> 00:00:25,240
<i>I'll just cry.</i>

6
00:00:25,320 --> 00:00:27,160
Once I'm done crying, I'll start over.

7
00:00:27,240 --> 00:00:29,440
What would it take to make you quit?

8
00:00:29,520 --> 00:00:33,320
<i>Maybe if Qin told me to stop</i>
<i>and chased me out of his plane.</i>

9
00:00:33,400 --> 00:00:35,640
<i>With how he's pursuing you,</i>
<i>are you uncomfortable?</i>

10
00:00:36,200 --> 00:00:37,080
<i>No.</i>

11
00:00:37,160 --> 00:00:39,400
<i>This lover boy</i>
<i>might just have a chance.</i>

12
00:00:39,480 --> 00:00:43,080
I'd like you to dance at
the opening for the open house.

13
00:00:43,160 --> 00:00:47,080
<i>I knew you'd be lonely.</i>
<i>That's why I got you a partner.</i>

14
00:00:47,160 --> 00:00:51,000
I really can't do this.
I could ruin everything.

15
00:00:51,080 --> 00:00:54,280
One more thing. You won't be alone.

16
00:00:54,360 --> 00:00:55,880
I knew you'd feel lonely.

17
00:00:55,960 --> 00:00:57,800
That's why I got you a partner.

18
00:00:57,880 --> 00:01:00,520
What? I really can't do this.

19
00:01:00,600 --> 00:01:01,920
It's that guy over there.

20
00:01:02,720 --> 00:01:04,080
Hey! How did you get in here?

21
00:01:04,160 --> 00:01:06,240
Get out! We're practicing!

22
00:01:09,960 --> 00:01:11,320
Okay, I can do it!

23
00:01:11,400 --> 00:01:12,280
- Sign me up.
- Really?

24
00:01:12,360 --> 00:01:14,040
Let me call my professor real quick.

25
00:01:14,120 --> 00:01:15,480
Don't change your mind, okay?

26
00:01:15,560 --> 00:01:16,800
Let's do this.

27
00:01:16,880 --> 00:01:19,000
Let's…

28
00:01:20,480 --> 00:01:22,920
Wait, you two
already know each other, right?

29
00:01:24,400 --> 00:01:25,760
- We don't.
- We do.

30
00:01:25,840 --> 00:01:28,240
What's going on?

31
00:01:28,320 --> 00:01:29,880
That's okay.

32
00:01:29,960 --> 00:01:32,600
Now you two know each other, right?

33
00:01:32,680 --> 00:01:35,040
And soon, you'll be
rehearsing together a lot.

34
00:01:35,120 --> 00:01:36,920
I didn't say I'd do this.

35
00:01:37,640 --> 00:01:39,560
Come on, Qin. Help us out.

36
00:01:39,640 --> 00:01:43,680
You made the crowd go wild
at Freshy Night.

37
00:01:44,240 --> 00:01:46,480
Plus, the professor specifically
asked for you.

38
00:01:46,560 --> 00:01:47,520
Yeah.

39
00:01:47,600 --> 00:01:50,280
You filled in for Ohm, and he said

40
00:01:50,360 --> 00:01:52,760
you enjoy singing, right?

41
00:01:52,840 --> 00:01:57,840
So I feel like this is a perfect
opportunity for you to perform onstage?

42
00:01:58,840 --> 00:01:59,760
I never said that.

43
00:02:02,440 --> 00:02:04,840
Qin, don't be too hasty.

44
00:02:04,920 --> 00:02:08,199
How about we give you
the details of the ceremony first?

45
00:02:09,520 --> 00:02:12,880
See you at the practice room
at 5:00 p.m., okay?

46
00:02:24,360 --> 00:02:25,840
Not changing your mind?

47
00:02:26,400 --> 00:02:28,000
I'm not.

48
00:02:28,080 --> 00:02:29,080
See you soon.

49
00:02:29,640 --> 00:02:30,600
Bye-bye.

50
00:04:00,160 --> 00:04:02,920
Is Qin going to come?
Is he going to be here?

51
00:04:03,480 --> 00:04:04,720
Is he?

52
00:04:05,640 --> 00:04:06,800
Will be come?

53
00:04:16,880 --> 00:04:19,800
- I thought you wouldn't show up.
- I'm here to tell them no.

54
00:04:21,160 --> 00:04:22,079
Move.

55
00:04:23,320 --> 00:04:24,840
- Why?
- Move.

56
00:04:35,480 --> 00:04:37,240
Here already?

57
00:04:45,120 --> 00:04:47,520
Okay, you all made it here
at the same time.

58
00:04:47,600 --> 00:04:50,040
This is Duang, and this is Qin.

59
00:04:50,120 --> 00:04:51,480
They're gonna join us on stage.

60
00:04:51,560 --> 00:04:54,160
So I'd like you guys
to get to know each other.

61
00:04:55,640 --> 00:04:58,320
- Duang, decorative arts student.
- A decorative arts student?

62
00:04:59,960 --> 00:05:02,080
Qin, I think
you already know Peem and Sol,

63
00:05:02,160 --> 00:05:03,160
voice students.

64
00:05:07,560 --> 00:05:08,440
I don't.

65
00:05:09,680 --> 00:05:11,600
You're a jazz student.

66
00:05:11,680 --> 00:05:13,400
No wonder you don't know them.

67
00:05:13,480 --> 00:05:15,680
Why'd you bring a jazz student on board?

68
00:05:15,760 --> 00:05:17,440
For a jazz performance?

69
00:05:19,480 --> 00:05:22,080
Come on, Peem. Why did you say that?

70
00:05:22,640 --> 00:05:24,960
It's nothing. I thought he was

71
00:05:25,520 --> 00:05:26,680
chosen for his looks…

72
00:05:28,400 --> 00:05:29,800
not his talent.

73
00:05:32,280 --> 00:05:35,040
You filled in for Ohm
at Freshy Night, right?

74
00:05:35,760 --> 00:05:38,840
Remember? They couldn't find you,

75
00:05:39,560 --> 00:05:40,680
so they went with him.

76
00:05:44,280 --> 00:05:45,760
Good for you. You can sing.

77
00:05:46,320 --> 00:05:47,440
Not entirely shitty.

78
00:05:47,520 --> 00:05:48,680
What does that mean?

79
00:05:50,160 --> 00:05:53,320
What's someone like you
doing here, anyway? Singing?

80
00:05:53,400 --> 00:05:54,520
Dancing?

81
00:05:54,600 --> 00:05:56,920
I don't think so.

82
00:05:58,360 --> 00:06:02,040
I guess your looks got you here.

83
00:06:02,960 --> 00:06:04,080
Was that a compliment?

84
00:06:04,160 --> 00:06:05,480
Shut it.

85
00:06:06,800 --> 00:06:08,040
I came here to quit.

86
00:06:09,000 --> 00:06:12,120
If you know that you're bad,

87
00:06:12,200 --> 00:06:13,600
then just give up already.

88
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:19,480
Thank you for giving me the drive.

89
00:06:19,960 --> 00:06:21,400
I've changed my mind.

90
00:06:29,720 --> 00:06:32,280
I guess it all worked out
in the end. Good.

91
00:06:34,440 --> 00:06:36,080
Let's get started, shall we?

92
00:06:36,160 --> 00:06:38,360
We'll go with the time-tested method.

93
00:06:38,440 --> 00:06:42,600
Time for a draw!
Here, bring in the box.

94
00:06:43,160 --> 00:06:44,240
I won't work with them.

95
00:06:44,320 --> 00:06:45,840
Did you ask what I wanted?

96
00:06:49,040 --> 00:06:51,080
But this method is super fair.

97
00:06:51,640 --> 00:06:54,840
I'm fine with it on one condition.
Put me with him.

98
00:06:59,720 --> 00:07:00,880
Shit!

99
00:07:03,680 --> 00:07:04,640
High-five!

100
00:07:04,720 --> 00:07:05,760
What a relief.

101
00:07:05,840 --> 00:07:08,040
I don't want to pair up with you either.

102
00:07:11,560 --> 00:07:13,880
No more draws.

103
00:07:13,960 --> 00:07:16,360
Allow me to explain the performance.

104
00:07:16,440 --> 00:07:19,640
Each pair will be doing two performances.

105
00:07:19,720 --> 00:07:21,000
Singing and dancing.

106
00:07:21,080 --> 00:07:24,440
That's why I asked you
if you're available this Sunday.

107
00:07:24,520 --> 00:07:27,400
We'll set up a practice schedule.

108
00:07:28,160 --> 00:07:29,920
We're available every day.

109
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:31,280
Right?

110
00:07:31,760 --> 00:07:33,000
I never said I was.

111
00:07:35,760 --> 00:07:37,360
Scared of looking like an idiot?

112
00:07:37,440 --> 00:07:40,760
Or just bad at singing?
How about playing music?

113
00:07:40,840 --> 00:07:43,840
The performances involve
singing and dancing though.

114
00:07:44,320 --> 00:07:46,880
- You sure you're up for this?
- Hey.

115
00:07:47,440 --> 00:07:48,480
Bit condescending, no?

116
00:07:51,000 --> 00:07:52,760
Okay, to put it simply,

117
00:07:52,840 --> 00:07:57,400
each pair will look for songs
you want to perform.

118
00:07:57,480 --> 00:07:58,840
It can be any song.

119
00:07:58,920 --> 00:08:01,840
In the next meeting,
we'll pick a few for the performance

120
00:08:01,920 --> 00:08:03,800
before proceeding to the next steps.

121
00:08:03,880 --> 00:08:06,120
Okay? That's it for today. Dismissed.

122
00:08:50,960 --> 00:08:51,880
Let's have dinner.

123
00:08:52,680 --> 00:08:53,800
Sure.

124
00:08:57,880 --> 00:08:59,520
Are you asking me out to dinner?

125
00:09:09,560 --> 00:09:10,440
Let's go!

126
00:09:20,080 --> 00:09:22,920
The food here is great,
but no air-con. Is that okay?

127
00:09:23,400 --> 00:09:24,320
Yes.

128
00:09:26,080 --> 00:09:28,400
What do you want to have?
I'll order it for you.

129
00:09:28,960 --> 00:09:32,200
I knew it! It's you, Duang!

130
00:09:32,280 --> 00:09:33,720
Hello, Auntie.

131
00:09:33,800 --> 00:09:35,280
And who's this?

132
00:09:35,360 --> 00:09:36,400
This boy.

133
00:09:36,480 --> 00:09:37,920
- Who is he?
- He's my…

134
00:09:38,480 --> 00:09:40,680
- A what?
- My friend.

135
00:09:40,760 --> 00:09:43,680
- Are you sure?
- Yes.

136
00:09:44,160 --> 00:09:46,520
Yes. But I hope
we'll become more than that.

137
00:09:46,600 --> 00:09:48,840
All right.

138
00:09:48,920 --> 00:09:50,800
Two of the garlic shrimp with rice.

139
00:09:53,600 --> 00:09:54,800
You ordered one for me?

140
00:09:56,720 --> 00:09:58,840
- Here we go.
- That's my order.

141
00:10:01,200 --> 00:10:03,200
His wants two.

142
00:10:03,280 --> 00:10:05,240
And the same for me.

143
00:10:05,320 --> 00:10:06,720
So that's four then.

144
00:10:08,760 --> 00:10:09,840
- Four servings?
- Yes.

145
00:10:09,920 --> 00:10:13,560
Hungry today, hey?
That's nice. You'll have energy.

146
00:10:13,640 --> 00:10:16,960
Sit tight, boys. Just a moment, please.

147
00:10:36,640 --> 00:10:39,080
The wind of love, it's blowing.

148
00:10:45,640 --> 00:10:47,840
What? Where are you going?

149
00:10:56,080 --> 00:10:58,520
Let me do it. You can wait at the table.

150
00:11:06,120 --> 00:11:08,080
Two cups for you?

151
00:11:11,640 --> 00:11:12,960
I've got yours.

152
00:11:27,480 --> 00:11:28,520
Just go back.

153
00:11:30,080 --> 00:11:31,120
I will.

154
00:11:32,280 --> 00:11:33,640
I'll help.

155
00:11:56,360 --> 00:11:58,320
It's nothing. I can do it myself.

156
00:11:58,800 --> 00:11:59,720
Hands off.

157
00:12:16,480 --> 00:12:18,200
Why did you change your mind?

158
00:12:20,080 --> 00:12:23,320
Beating them at their own game
is the ultimate revenge.

159
00:12:24,480 --> 00:12:28,040
That's the spirit!
I will not let you down.

160
00:12:28,120 --> 00:12:31,720
I'll practice hard
and perfect the performance for you.

161
00:12:31,800 --> 00:12:35,080
Everyone will like our performance.

162
00:12:39,880 --> 00:12:41,080
Why are you looking at me?

163
00:12:42,280 --> 00:12:45,920
You're adorable and…

164
00:12:49,640 --> 00:12:51,120
Are you waiting for my answer?

165
00:12:53,320 --> 00:12:55,000
I'll can also ignore you.

166
00:12:56,080 --> 00:12:58,160
All right, here I go.

167
00:12:59,120 --> 00:13:01,880
So here's what I want to ask you.

168
00:13:01,960 --> 00:13:04,680
Is your dream really to be a singer?

169
00:13:11,040 --> 00:13:12,960
I know you can do it.

170
00:13:13,560 --> 00:13:18,280
You'll be the best singer I've ever known!

171
00:13:21,120 --> 00:13:22,760
Here you go!

172
00:13:22,840 --> 00:13:27,320
Four plates of garlic shrimp with rice.

173
00:13:27,400 --> 00:13:30,160
I'd be dead if you ordered and more.
Here you go.

174
00:13:30,240 --> 00:13:31,880
These are yours, Duang.

175
00:13:33,360 --> 00:13:35,000
These are yours, dear.

176
00:13:39,920 --> 00:13:43,400
I made you extra! Packed with rice!

177
00:13:47,760 --> 00:13:48,720
I'm delighted.

178
00:13:51,680 --> 00:13:54,200
It's the first time
we're having dinner together.

179
00:13:54,280 --> 00:13:56,440
It's our special moment.

180
00:14:00,440 --> 00:14:02,720
Just shut up and eat.

181
00:14:02,800 --> 00:14:04,160
- Hey!
- Right.

182
00:14:05,480 --> 00:14:07,160
Feel free to get back to work.

183
00:14:08,240 --> 00:14:10,520
You're shooing me away?

184
00:14:10,600 --> 00:14:12,480
I guess you are. It's okay.

185
00:14:12,560 --> 00:14:16,080
I was being too nosy anyway.
Make yourselves at home.

186
00:14:21,320 --> 00:14:22,400
Let's dig in.

187
00:14:23,880 --> 00:14:25,400
Stop with that tone.

188
00:14:26,840 --> 00:14:29,040
I can't do that.
You're not just anyone.

189
00:14:29,120 --> 00:14:31,160
You are my special one.

190
00:14:31,240 --> 00:14:32,640
<i>You're…</i>

191
00:14:32,720 --> 00:14:34,160
Ever been smacked by a shrimp?

192
00:14:49,680 --> 00:14:51,600
A spoon and a fork go together…

193
00:15:09,480 --> 00:15:10,880
Where are you going?

194
00:15:13,120 --> 00:15:14,560
Let me take you home.

195
00:15:15,800 --> 00:15:17,000
I called a ride.

196
00:15:17,840 --> 00:15:20,520
Well… Let me join you.

197
00:15:28,080 --> 00:15:29,200
Well…

198
00:15:30,080 --> 00:15:32,800
I'll just see you off here then.

199
00:15:36,080 --> 00:15:37,120
Hey.

200
00:15:39,120 --> 00:15:40,320
Care for a game?

201
00:15:40,760 --> 00:15:41,600
Another one?

202
00:15:42,800 --> 00:15:45,320
Do you know what a door's biggest fear is?

203
00:15:49,440 --> 00:15:50,840
It's fire

204
00:15:51,360 --> 00:15:54,520
because it's smol-door-ingly hot!

205
00:15:55,800 --> 00:15:56,640
Not funny.

206
00:15:59,040 --> 00:16:01,600
Anything you wanna ask me?

207
00:16:02,920 --> 00:16:03,960
No.

208
00:16:05,200 --> 00:16:07,680
You didn't even think about it, did you?

209
00:16:13,840 --> 00:16:15,360
See you tomorrow!

210
00:16:41,560 --> 00:16:44,080
Guys. Yesterday,

211
00:16:44,640 --> 00:16:46,120
we were like this.

212
00:16:46,920 --> 00:16:48,600
We were this close.

213
00:16:57,320 --> 00:16:59,800
<i>Like I could almost kiss him.</i>

214
00:17:00,280 --> 00:17:02,080
Qin even let me see him off.

215
00:17:03,600 --> 00:17:06,440
I felt like a handsome, cute boy,

216
00:17:07,520 --> 00:17:08,839
acting as his bodyguard.

217
00:17:12,560 --> 00:17:14,640
Hey! Were you listening to me?

218
00:17:14,720 --> 00:17:16,960
Did you have to hit me?

219
00:17:17,520 --> 00:17:19,000
I was!

220
00:17:19,560 --> 00:17:22,160
His bodyguard? Nonsense.

221
00:17:23,160 --> 00:17:27,160
I wasn't talking nonsense.
Stop saying that.

222
00:17:27,240 --> 00:17:29,800
- It's true.
- You're way too optimistic.

223
00:17:29,880 --> 00:17:31,760
You're the "Overly Optimistic Lover Boy."

224
00:17:31,840 --> 00:17:34,000
Being optimistic makes it fun.

225
00:17:34,080 --> 00:17:37,120
Sure, lover boy.

226
00:17:37,200 --> 00:17:38,840
What about uni, yeah?

227
00:17:38,920 --> 00:17:40,280
Your project is almost due.

228
00:17:40,360 --> 00:17:43,600
Yeah, he's right. We'll be doomed
if we listen to your stories.

229
00:17:43,680 --> 00:17:46,480
What? You're blaming me for this?

230
00:17:46,560 --> 00:17:47,640
<i>We ate together.</i>

231
00:17:48,200 --> 00:17:50,040
Come on, that's too short, isn't it?

232
00:17:50,120 --> 00:17:52,960
It didn't feel like
you were there with lover boy.

233
00:17:53,040 --> 00:17:54,800
Don't ask me then.

234
00:17:54,880 --> 00:17:56,960
By the way, did Duang take you home?

235
00:17:57,040 --> 00:17:58,000
Did you get close?

236
00:17:58,080 --> 00:17:59,280
Did you fall for him?

237
00:18:01,280 --> 00:18:02,760
Shut up, or no more studying.

238
00:18:04,360 --> 00:18:05,240
Okay.

239
00:18:05,800 --> 00:18:06,640
Please continue.

240
00:18:07,280 --> 00:18:08,320
"Exercise One.

241
00:18:08,400 --> 00:18:12,080
Fill in the notes
in the spaces below the asterisks."

242
00:18:12,680 --> 00:18:13,640
What do you think?

243
00:18:14,480 --> 00:18:16,880
<i>So here's what I want to ask you.</i>

244
00:18:17,440 --> 00:18:19,800
Is your dream really to be a singer?

245
00:18:21,440 --> 00:18:22,880
I know you can do it.

246
00:18:22,960 --> 00:18:27,720
You'll be the best singer I've ever known!

247
00:18:34,800 --> 00:18:35,680
Qin?

248
00:18:36,280 --> 00:18:37,200
Qin.

249
00:18:37,800 --> 00:18:38,960
Hey, Qin.

250
00:18:40,640 --> 00:18:41,560
The exercise.

251
00:18:41,640 --> 00:18:43,800
- The first one.
- What?

252
00:18:43,880 --> 00:18:46,400
The first one,
the one Tong just read out loud.

253
00:18:46,480 --> 00:18:49,440
- Stop spacing out and continue.
- What was it?

254
00:18:49,520 --> 00:18:51,160
He just read the exercise to you.

255
00:18:57,320 --> 00:18:59,640
The song for our dance performance will be

256
00:18:59,720 --> 00:19:00,640
"Not the Best."

257
00:19:01,840 --> 00:19:02,680
Perfect.

258
00:19:02,760 --> 00:19:04,840
Good choice.
What do you think, Alice?

259
00:19:05,480 --> 00:19:08,760
I'm cool with that.
I like it. That's great.

260
00:19:09,480 --> 00:19:10,400
Me likey too.

261
00:19:14,120 --> 00:19:17,200
But I'm worried about you two

262
00:19:17,280 --> 00:19:20,320
because the song's fairly fast-paced.
So are you sure?

263
00:19:21,000 --> 00:19:24,000
I agree.
I'm also not that great at dancing.

264
00:19:24,080 --> 00:19:25,880
But with practice, we'll manage.

265
00:19:27,240 --> 00:19:29,400
Should we give it a try?

266
00:19:30,240 --> 00:19:33,160
Great idea!
This will give us a clear picture.

267
00:19:33,240 --> 00:19:37,040
Duang told me he's quite bad at dancing.

268
00:19:37,120 --> 00:19:40,360
I didn't know why he was being so humble.

269
00:19:40,440 --> 00:19:43,360
All right. Let's get to it.
Set the floor on fire.

270
00:19:43,440 --> 00:19:45,240
Come on, get up.

271
00:19:45,320 --> 00:19:46,800
- Right.
- Let's go.

272
00:19:53,320 --> 00:19:54,920
One, two, three.

273
00:19:55,000 --> 00:19:56,760
<i>A shark washes ashore</i>

274
00:19:56,840 --> 00:19:59,520
<i>Four, five, six</i>
<i>A gecko is stuffed full</i>

275
00:19:59,600 --> 00:20:02,240
<i>I'm like jelly</i>
<i>Dancing like a beating heart</i>

276
00:20:02,320 --> 00:20:05,480
<i>I'm falling because of this…</i>

277
00:20:05,960 --> 00:20:07,080
This guy!

278
00:20:13,560 --> 00:20:16,520
You're the lead singer, right?
So you must like singing.

279
00:20:17,440 --> 00:20:20,080
Do you want me to sing,
so I can make this even worse?

280
00:20:21,200 --> 00:20:22,080
Hey.

281
00:20:22,160 --> 00:20:24,160
You can't be that bad.

282
00:20:26,480 --> 00:20:28,480
It's only going to get worse.

283
00:20:36,080 --> 00:20:38,200
<i>There's this one friend</i>

284
00:20:38,280 --> 00:20:41,800
<i>Who has a crush</i>
<i>But never sends them a message</i>

285
00:20:42,320 --> 00:20:47,520
<i>There's this one friend</i>
<i>Who always gets rejected</i>

286
00:20:48,280 --> 00:20:50,320
<i>There's this one friend</i>

287
00:20:50,400 --> 00:20:54,000
<i>You look over and disregard</i>

288
00:20:54,080 --> 00:20:59,000
<i>You never think about</i>
<i>This little friend of yours</i>

289
00:20:59,080 --> 00:21:01,160
<i>Even though their love is sincere</i>

290
00:21:01,240 --> 00:21:04,440
<i>They'd never leave or abandon you</i>

291
00:21:12,920 --> 00:21:15,680
<i>Would it bother you if</i>

292
00:21:15,760 --> 00:21:19,240
<i>They kept finding excuses to be near you?</i>

293
00:21:19,320 --> 00:21:21,440
<i>Would this close be okay?</i>

294
00:21:21,520 --> 00:21:25,440
<i>That's right</i>
<i>'Cause that little friend is me</i>

295
00:21:26,280 --> 00:21:28,200
That's pretty good.

296
00:21:28,280 --> 00:21:30,520
It's decent, actually.
Who says you're tone-deaf?

297
00:21:31,240 --> 00:21:33,360
A horrible friend of mine.

298
00:21:33,920 --> 00:21:36,320
Singing is no longer a concern.

299
00:21:36,800 --> 00:21:39,200
As for dancing,
Qin, can you take care of him?

300
00:21:43,240 --> 00:21:44,520
I'll do my best.

301
00:21:44,600 --> 00:21:47,360
Qin, I'm going to leave him to you, okay?

302
00:21:47,440 --> 00:21:48,360
Don't worry, guys.

303
00:21:48,440 --> 00:21:51,240
Qin is the best, I guarantee.

304
00:21:51,800 --> 00:21:52,720
Enough.

305
00:21:54,960 --> 00:21:57,080
Whatever you say,

306
00:21:57,160 --> 00:21:59,120
I'll make it happen.

307
00:22:01,600 --> 00:22:02,480
Okay, so…

308
00:22:02,560 --> 00:22:05,680
Qin, I think you have what it takes.

309
00:22:05,760 --> 00:22:08,400
As for Duang,

310
00:22:08,480 --> 00:22:10,680
you have the basics that might not be

311
00:22:10,760 --> 00:22:12,320
the worst.

312
00:22:14,960 --> 00:22:18,600
With some practice, you'll be good to go.

313
00:22:19,320 --> 00:22:22,400
Qin, which song are you going to sing?

314
00:22:23,840 --> 00:22:25,720
How about…

315
00:22:25,800 --> 00:22:28,880
"Sing Tee Saen Dee,"
a song by Tattoo Colour.

316
00:22:31,440 --> 00:22:32,560
Sure. I like this song.

317
00:22:32,640 --> 00:22:34,200
I like it too.

318
00:22:38,080 --> 00:22:39,880
Okay, to sum this up.

319
00:22:39,960 --> 00:22:42,480
It's<i> "</i>Not the Best"
and "Sing Tee Saen Dee<i>." </i>Okay?

320
00:22:42,560 --> 00:22:44,600
- Yes.
- Okay.

321
00:23:19,760 --> 00:23:23,000
PODDUANG LIKED YOUR PHOTO

322
00:23:23,080 --> 00:23:26,280
PODDUANG LIKED YOUR PHOTO

323
00:23:33,960 --> 00:23:35,840
FOLLOW BACK

324
00:23:35,920 --> 00:23:37,520
SEE PROFILE

325
00:23:40,640 --> 00:23:42,360
This is Duang.

326
00:23:42,440 --> 00:23:43,960
This is Qin.

327
00:23:44,040 --> 00:23:46,080
A perfect match!

328
00:23:46,920 --> 00:23:47,840
Click!

329
00:24:08,080 --> 00:24:10,520
QIN SENT YOU A MESSAGE

330
00:24:18,960 --> 00:24:21,080
<i>I've rearranged the song.</i>
<i>Let's practice it later.</i>

331
00:24:21,160 --> 00:24:22,000
What?

332
00:24:28,040 --> 00:24:30,640
<i>Guys! Qin just messaged me.</i>

333
00:24:31,760 --> 00:24:33,920
<i>I'm gonna pass out! Need an inhaler.</i>

334
00:24:38,840 --> 00:24:40,360
<i>You're ridiculous.</i>

335
00:24:41,560 --> 00:24:43,640
<i>Fine. Did you reply to his message?</i>

336
00:24:44,720 --> 00:24:47,280
<i>He must like me too.</i>
<i>He just texted me.</i>

337
00:24:49,000 --> 00:24:51,320
<i>Then reply to him.</i>
<i>Don't make him change his mind.</i>

338
00:25:09,680 --> 00:25:12,840
This sucks. He changed his mind!

339
00:25:21,280 --> 00:25:22,720
<i>Hey.</i>

340
00:25:23,200 --> 00:25:25,480
<i>Have you finished rearranging the song?</i>

341
00:25:25,560 --> 00:25:27,480
<i>Can I listen to it?</i>

342
00:25:27,560 --> 00:25:29,520
<i>Hey!</i>

343
00:25:29,600 --> 00:25:31,520
<i>Come back and talk to me!</i>

344
00:25:32,280 --> 00:25:34,080
<i>I was too late.</i>

345
00:25:48,280 --> 00:25:51,320
He's not replying!

346
00:25:58,480 --> 00:26:00,400
- The exam's over!
- Finally.

347
00:26:02,680 --> 00:26:05,800
Hey, how was it?
Did you keep chatting with Qin last night?

348
00:26:06,840 --> 00:26:07,760
I did!

349
00:26:07,840 --> 00:26:08,880
Last night…

350
00:26:08,960 --> 00:26:11,560
We chatted all night.

351
00:26:11,640 --> 00:26:12,840
Right.

352
00:26:13,320 --> 00:26:15,200
Let me see the messages.

353
00:26:15,280 --> 00:26:18,400
That was only 10% true. Look.

354
00:26:18,480 --> 00:26:22,000
You were basically
in the very last row of economy.

355
00:26:27,680 --> 00:26:28,800
I know!

356
00:26:28,880 --> 00:26:30,640
Tests are done, how about a drink?

357
00:26:30,720 --> 00:26:33,840
I'm like… I'm so thirsty.

358
00:26:38,960 --> 00:26:39,840
Stop.

359
00:26:42,320 --> 00:26:43,160
Let's go!

360
00:26:47,400 --> 00:26:48,960
So you guys aren't really coming?

361
00:26:50,800 --> 00:26:53,440
Of course we are. It's semester break.

362
00:26:54,000 --> 00:26:54,920
No classes.

363
00:26:55,000 --> 00:26:57,320
We no longer
have to come to the university!

364
00:26:57,400 --> 00:26:58,400
Hold up.

365
00:26:58,960 --> 00:27:00,400
What is it?

366
00:27:00,480 --> 00:27:02,120
What did you just say?

367
00:27:02,200 --> 00:27:04,360
- It's semester break.
- Yeah.

368
00:27:08,520 --> 00:27:11,880
I forgot about that.
I won't get to see Qin during break.

369
00:27:14,720 --> 00:27:19,160
Don't say I'm teaching
a fish how to swim, darling.

370
00:27:19,240 --> 00:27:20,640
If you want to see him,

371
00:27:20,720 --> 00:27:23,000
look for an excuse to.

372
00:27:23,080 --> 00:27:24,840
There are millions to choose from.

373
00:27:24,920 --> 00:27:27,040
Yeah. You stupid puppy.

374
00:27:31,280 --> 00:27:32,520
Now bark.

375
00:27:35,680 --> 00:27:36,600
Hey!

376
00:27:38,720 --> 00:27:39,600
Let's go.

377
00:27:40,320 --> 00:27:41,280
Come on.

378
00:27:41,360 --> 00:27:42,640
Your treat?

379
00:27:42,720 --> 00:27:44,880
- What?
- Drinks on you?

380
00:27:44,960 --> 00:27:45,880
Shut it!

381
00:27:52,560 --> 00:27:54,760
What? Let's go. Why did you stop?

382
00:27:57,040 --> 00:27:58,440
Huh? What's wrong?

383
00:27:58,920 --> 00:27:59,800
Hey!

384
00:28:01,040 --> 00:28:02,240
What's gotten into you?

385
00:28:02,320 --> 00:28:03,840
All you want to do is fall over

386
00:28:03,920 --> 00:28:07,080
and plant your face on the ground.
You're just troubling others.

387
00:28:07,640 --> 00:28:09,840
You're not me. You wouldn't understand.

388
00:28:09,920 --> 00:28:12,640
- Right?
- Yeah! You have no clue!

389
00:28:14,800 --> 00:28:16,000
How exactly?

390
00:28:16,080 --> 00:28:17,000
What was that?

391
00:28:19,360 --> 00:28:21,040
Hey, lover boy.

392
00:28:22,000 --> 00:28:23,720
What's wrong? You look like a sad puppy.

393
00:28:23,800 --> 00:28:25,400
Hey, don't dig it into him.

394
00:28:25,480 --> 00:28:27,040
You're gonna make it worse.

395
00:28:29,320 --> 00:28:31,400
So why are you upset?

396
00:28:31,480 --> 00:28:32,440
It's semester break.

397
00:28:33,000 --> 00:28:36,240
He won't get to see Qin,
so he's looking so heartbroken.

398
00:28:38,280 --> 00:28:39,160
Oh, Duang.

399
00:28:40,120 --> 00:28:41,000
Perfect.

400
00:28:41,080 --> 00:28:42,480
- Ask his friend.
- Yeah.

401
00:28:42,560 --> 00:28:43,440
Perfect timing.

402
00:28:44,280 --> 00:28:45,160
Yeah!

403
00:28:46,080 --> 00:28:48,280
I have a question.

404
00:28:48,360 --> 00:28:50,000
What I want to ask you is…

405
00:28:57,440 --> 00:28:58,360
Gosh!

406
00:28:59,040 --> 00:29:00,360
I'll do the talking.

407
00:29:00,880 --> 00:29:01,720
So,

408
00:29:02,440 --> 00:29:03,520
Qin…

409
00:29:04,080 --> 00:29:05,240
He…

410
00:29:06,080 --> 00:29:07,320
He…

411
00:29:07,880 --> 00:29:10,160
He…

412
00:29:10,920 --> 00:29:12,040
- He--
- Gosh!

413
00:29:13,720 --> 00:29:14,920
When are you going to start?

414
00:29:15,480 --> 00:29:16,480
Right about now.

415
00:29:20,720 --> 00:29:22,000
He…

416
00:29:22,080 --> 00:29:23,560
Where is he going for break?

417
00:29:30,080 --> 00:29:31,080
No clue.

418
00:29:31,160 --> 00:29:32,480
We don't hang out during break.

419
00:29:33,560 --> 00:29:35,680
- How upsetting.
- But tonight, we'll be at the bar.

420
00:29:37,640 --> 00:29:39,640
X's bar. Do you know it?

421
00:29:40,840 --> 00:29:42,880
X's! Okay, see you at X's.

422
00:29:42,960 --> 00:29:44,240
Let's go get changed!

423
00:29:44,320 --> 00:29:45,600
- Let's go.
- Hey, wait!

424
00:29:45,680 --> 00:29:46,720
What time?

425
00:29:46,800 --> 00:29:48,800
- What time?
- Yeah, when?

426
00:29:50,240 --> 00:29:51,080
Around 8:00 p.m.

427
00:29:52,080 --> 00:29:53,360
8:00 p.m.

428
00:29:53,440 --> 00:29:55,680
Yeah, nerds drink early. Come on!

429
00:29:55,760 --> 00:29:58,280
- Thank you!
- Say that again and I won't help you.

430
00:30:00,080 --> 00:30:01,520
You're such a baddie.

431
00:30:01,600 --> 00:30:02,440
- Yeah!
- Yeah.

432
00:30:17,320 --> 00:30:18,840
That's Qin's table.

433
00:30:24,240 --> 00:30:26,720
Hey. Can I sit with you?

434
00:30:27,320 --> 00:30:28,160
No.

435
00:30:30,400 --> 00:30:33,680
Minus 100,000 points for our lover boy.

436
00:30:34,800 --> 00:30:37,240
The table next to yours will do.

437
00:30:40,280 --> 00:30:42,600
Plus 100,000 points for our lover boy.

438
00:30:46,080 --> 00:30:49,200
Qin gave me a nod!
I'm going to pass out.

439
00:30:49,280 --> 00:30:50,520
Hey!

440
00:30:50,600 --> 00:30:52,560
Don't die just yet. It's only started.

441
00:30:53,720 --> 00:30:54,680
I'll call the staff.

442
00:30:54,760 --> 00:30:55,640
Excuse me.

443
00:30:55,720 --> 00:30:57,240
Can we sit here?

444
00:30:57,320 --> 00:30:58,800
- That one's reserved.
- What?

445
00:31:02,080 --> 00:31:03,800
It's X. Go see him.

446
00:31:03,880 --> 00:31:04,960
Talk to X.

447
00:31:05,520 --> 00:31:06,800
X!

448
00:31:17,560 --> 00:31:20,480
So I want that table.

449
00:31:22,680 --> 00:31:23,560
It's reserved.

450
00:31:24,720 --> 00:31:27,360
Only two tables are available. This one

451
00:31:27,880 --> 00:31:28,720
and that one.

452
00:31:33,520 --> 00:31:36,320
I'm going with the first one.

453
00:31:37,440 --> 00:31:38,800
I'm sorry, but it's occupied.

454
00:31:39,520 --> 00:31:40,760
You're too slow.

455
00:31:43,680 --> 00:31:45,920
That one's still available. Hurry.

456
00:31:46,000 --> 00:31:47,440
Chop-chop.

457
00:32:01,200 --> 00:32:02,560
Order some drinks already.

458
00:32:03,320 --> 00:32:04,520
You do it.

459
00:32:11,480 --> 00:32:12,360
Gosh…

460
00:32:12,440 --> 00:32:15,280
You look like a sad puppy
that got abandoned mid-flight.

461
00:32:15,840 --> 00:32:17,600
You can still see Qin from here.

462
00:32:18,640 --> 00:32:19,880
It's too far.

463
00:32:19,960 --> 00:32:21,080
You don't get it.

464
00:32:22,480 --> 00:32:24,960
That's why I told you
to hurry and talk to X,

465
00:32:25,040 --> 00:32:26,960
yet you chose to meander.

466
00:32:27,040 --> 00:32:28,960
What the hell do you want me to do?

467
00:32:29,480 --> 00:32:32,680
I won't be seeing him during the break.
What should I do?

468
00:32:38,720 --> 00:32:40,080
Duang?

469
00:32:41,240 --> 00:32:43,440
Are you guys celebrating
the end of the exams?

470
00:32:48,800 --> 00:32:49,960
Alice and Tinn?

471
00:32:50,600 --> 00:32:53,040
Guys, take a seat.
I want to talk to you.

472
00:32:54,080 --> 00:32:54,960
So,

473
00:32:55,040 --> 00:32:58,000
can we practice during the break?
Would you guys mind?

474
00:32:58,080 --> 00:32:59,640
I still can't sing or dance.

475
00:32:59,720 --> 00:33:01,120
I'm afraid I'll be fall behind.

476
00:33:01,200 --> 00:33:03,080
The performance won't turn out great,

477
00:33:03,160 --> 00:33:04,880
and I might end up ruining the show.

478
00:33:06,880 --> 00:33:08,000
Yeah, you're right.

479
00:33:08,080 --> 00:33:09,440
I totally forgot that

480
00:33:09,520 --> 00:33:11,600
you have some free time during the break.

481
00:33:11,680 --> 00:33:13,160
But, Duang, are you--

482
00:33:13,240 --> 00:33:15,200
I'm very much free.

483
00:33:16,760 --> 00:33:17,680
That's nice, actually.

484
00:33:18,440 --> 00:33:20,480
We'll tell Qin about practice.

485
00:33:21,680 --> 00:33:24,040
That's excellent!
Thank you very much.

486
00:33:24,120 --> 00:33:25,800
That's great. Thank you.

487
00:33:25,880 --> 00:33:27,320
Thank you, Alice.

488
00:33:27,400 --> 00:33:30,040
Thank you, Tinn. A round of applause!

489
00:33:30,120 --> 00:33:32,240
Thank you.

490
00:33:47,160 --> 00:33:48,560
I've missed you.

491
00:34:05,720 --> 00:34:07,600
Thank you for coming, guys.

492
00:34:07,680 --> 00:34:11,159
We have something to tell you.

493
00:34:11,719 --> 00:34:16,480
We requested the professor for
extra practice sessions during the break.

494
00:34:16,560 --> 00:34:19,120
That's why we're able
to rent this practice room.

495
00:34:19,679 --> 00:34:22,600
That's why I want to see you dance
to the choreography I sent you.

496
00:34:22,679 --> 00:34:24,880
But both of us are busy.

497
00:34:24,960 --> 00:34:26,120
He's right.

498
00:34:27,600 --> 00:34:28,440
How about this?

499
00:34:28,520 --> 00:34:32,440
If you've already nailed it,
you can skip practice.

500
00:34:34,480 --> 00:34:37,080
I think we're doing just fine.

501
00:34:37,159 --> 00:34:39,600
- We can practice after the break.
- Yeah.

502
00:34:40,360 --> 00:34:42,120
Sure thing.

503
00:34:42,600 --> 00:34:43,800
What about Duang and Qin?

504
00:34:44,800 --> 00:34:46,040
I still can't dance.

505
00:34:46,120 --> 00:34:49,920
Counting from one to seven to the beat,
I still can't do that.

506
00:34:51,560 --> 00:34:52,679
Qin…

507
00:34:52,760 --> 00:34:55,800
Are you available? This isn't required.

508
00:35:03,320 --> 00:35:04,560
How about this?

509
00:35:04,640 --> 00:35:06,040
For the sake of fairness,

510
00:35:06,120 --> 00:35:08,240
I want to see how you guys do right now.

511
00:35:08,320 --> 00:35:10,960
If it's okay,
no need for the extra sessions.

512
00:35:11,040 --> 00:35:13,200
Should we start
with the dance performance?

513
00:35:13,280 --> 00:35:15,120
That's a great idea.

514
00:35:15,200 --> 00:35:18,400
This eagerness means that
you've been working hard, doesn't it?

515
00:35:18,480 --> 00:35:21,400
- That's right!
- Let's get to it then.

516
00:35:22,120 --> 00:35:23,120
Go.

517
00:35:28,120 --> 00:35:30,960
Let's go.
Let's show them what we can do.

518
00:35:33,280 --> 00:35:34,120
Come on.

519
00:35:43,320 --> 00:35:46,840
One, two, three, four, five, six…

520
00:35:49,680 --> 00:35:51,600
Wait. Stop.

521
00:35:51,680 --> 00:35:53,120
Stop. So…

522
00:35:53,920 --> 00:35:56,240
forget everything I just told you.

523
00:35:56,320 --> 00:35:58,520
How many months do you have to practice?

524
00:35:59,600 --> 00:36:01,920
Until the semester starts.

525
00:36:06,440 --> 00:36:09,960
Please practice with him during the break.

526
00:36:10,040 --> 00:36:12,600
I beg you.
At least three times a week will do.

527
00:36:14,840 --> 00:36:15,840
Good luck, boys.

528
00:36:16,520 --> 00:36:18,160
Gosh, they're going to need it.

529
00:36:20,360 --> 00:36:21,200
Excuse me.

530
00:36:21,760 --> 00:36:23,800
Can we leave now?

531
00:36:23,880 --> 00:36:26,560
I don't think we need to do anything now.

532
00:36:26,640 --> 00:36:29,960
If you think you're fine,
feel free to leave.

533
00:36:30,520 --> 00:36:31,840
Okay.

534
00:36:31,920 --> 00:36:33,560
By the way,

535
00:36:33,640 --> 00:36:37,840
If possible,
at the ceremony, can we go first?

536
00:36:37,920 --> 00:36:40,120
I don't want to get embarrassed.

537
00:36:41,760 --> 00:36:42,800
Also,

538
00:36:42,880 --> 00:36:46,040
they want us to perform,
not ruin the show.

539
00:36:46,120 --> 00:36:47,120
Do you know that?

540
00:36:55,000 --> 00:36:57,160
Qin, please.

541
00:37:00,480 --> 00:37:01,360
Sure.

542
00:37:03,120 --> 00:37:05,080
I'll be practicing here
three times a week.

543
00:37:07,920 --> 00:37:09,440
Do you want to start now?

544
00:37:09,520 --> 00:37:11,000
Let's start now.

545
00:37:11,080 --> 00:37:12,920
Wait, we can't.

546
00:37:13,000 --> 00:37:15,840
- Tinn, we've got an errand to run.
- What errand?

547
00:37:16,880 --> 00:37:18,040
Come on. Think.

548
00:37:20,360 --> 00:37:21,760
We have a matter to attend to.

549
00:37:24,600 --> 00:37:27,560
Feel free to practice
on your own, you two.

550
00:37:27,640 --> 00:37:28,760
Okay?

551
00:37:28,840 --> 00:37:30,200
Sure thing.

552
00:37:32,840 --> 00:37:34,320
I'm going to the bathroom.

553
00:37:40,440 --> 00:37:41,800
Duang.

554
00:37:41,880 --> 00:37:46,520
I know that
you intentionally danced badly.

555
00:37:47,480 --> 00:37:48,880
No, I didn't.

556
00:37:48,960 --> 00:37:51,560
High-pitched? Is that so? Okay.

557
00:37:53,240 --> 00:37:57,560
The Faculty King I knew
still couldn't win Qin over.

558
00:37:57,640 --> 00:38:00,960
He was very dedicated,
yet he got rejected.

559
00:38:04,800 --> 00:38:09,440
However, it depends.

560
00:38:09,520 --> 00:38:11,400
You might be that person, you know?

561
00:38:16,560 --> 00:38:19,240
No, you're misunderstanding me.

562
00:38:19,320 --> 00:38:22,000
What I mean by that is

563
00:38:22,080 --> 00:38:24,360
you might be compatible with Qin.

564
00:38:25,440 --> 00:38:29,120
From the bottom of my heart,

565
00:38:29,200 --> 00:38:33,200
I've been supporting and rooting for you.

566
00:38:34,600 --> 00:38:36,800
Good luck, okay?

567
00:38:36,880 --> 00:38:39,120
- You've got this.
- Thank you.

568
00:38:39,200 --> 00:38:40,080
Let's go.

569
00:39:11,120 --> 00:39:12,960
Hey…

570
00:39:13,520 --> 00:39:15,960
What's wrong?
Is something troubling you?

571
00:39:16,960 --> 00:39:19,080
How did you know?

572
00:39:20,880 --> 00:39:23,040
You looked rather happy.
What the fuck happened?

573
00:39:25,520 --> 00:39:28,720
I'm fine, actually. I feel better now.

574
00:39:31,720 --> 00:39:33,720
It's because you were worried about me.

575
00:39:33,800 --> 00:39:35,680
When did I say that I was?

576
00:39:36,760 --> 00:39:38,000
Fine, you weren't.

577
00:39:38,080 --> 00:39:40,840
Asking me a question
already brightens up my day.

578
00:39:47,160 --> 00:39:50,520
Come on.
You don't care about me at all.

579
00:39:57,000 --> 00:39:59,080
QIN STARTED FOLLOWING YOU ON INSTAGRAM

580
00:40:01,200 --> 00:40:02,800
You followed me on Instagram?

581
00:40:03,360 --> 00:40:06,280
It's for discussing work. Nothing else.

582
00:40:08,080 --> 00:40:10,800
I'm delighted.

583
00:40:12,720 --> 00:40:15,960
Don't spam me with texts.
They annoy me.

584
00:40:22,440 --> 00:40:24,240
Are we going to practice or what?

585
00:40:36,280 --> 00:40:39,720
It'd be nice to have someone ride with me.

586
00:40:39,800 --> 00:40:41,320
So you want me to go with you?

587
00:40:41,400 --> 00:40:43,000
Or should I stay with you?

588
00:40:44,840 --> 00:40:45,840
You have a dirty mind.

589
00:40:45,920 --> 00:40:47,320
Go home on your own.

590
00:40:47,400 --> 00:40:48,600
I'll stop.

591
00:40:51,880 --> 00:40:54,960
I already called a ride.
If you're tired, just hail a cab.

592
00:40:56,280 --> 00:40:57,680
I'll DM you on Instagram, okay?

593
00:40:59,200 --> 00:41:00,760
I already told you not to--

594
00:41:30,400 --> 00:41:33,240
Duang? What brings you here?

595
00:41:33,320 --> 00:41:34,480
Jamie!

596
00:41:35,160 --> 00:41:37,200
- What?
- What should I do?

597
00:41:38,240 --> 00:41:39,120
What now?

598
00:41:41,280 --> 00:41:44,000
Alice told me that
it's hard to win Qin over.

599
00:41:44,080 --> 00:41:45,520
She also wished me luck.

600
00:41:47,560 --> 00:41:50,440
You just figured that out?
I thought you already knew that.

601
00:41:53,080 --> 00:41:57,120
All right. Serious talk.
Listen to me. I think this is weird.

602
00:41:57,680 --> 00:41:58,920
What's weird?

603
00:41:59,520 --> 00:42:01,080
Alice is an outsider.

604
00:42:01,160 --> 00:42:05,120
If she told you that,
you'd better brace yourself.

605
00:42:05,760 --> 00:42:08,960
Jamie. How would that be possible?

606
00:42:11,440 --> 00:42:15,120
I know that you've been doing a lot
and trying really hard.

607
00:42:15,200 --> 00:42:18,920
But that doesn't guarantee success.

608
00:42:19,480 --> 00:42:23,040
Still, you might at least
get something out of this.

609
00:42:24,080 --> 00:42:26,640
Yes! Qin followed me back on Instagram.

610
00:42:26,720 --> 00:42:27,720
See?

611
00:42:29,520 --> 00:42:31,400
I can only DM him for work though.

612
00:42:33,040 --> 00:42:34,280
You gonna do what he said?

613
00:42:34,360 --> 00:42:36,840
No. I spammed him with emojis.

614
00:42:36,920 --> 00:42:39,520
Right. It's time for a wake-up call.

615
00:42:39,600 --> 00:42:41,560
You need to start thinking about this.

616
00:42:41,640 --> 00:42:44,160
If he rejects you,

617
00:42:44,240 --> 00:42:47,560
or someone else comes into his life,

618
00:42:47,640 --> 00:42:49,080
you're going to get hurt.

619
00:42:49,160 --> 00:42:51,080
What are you saying?

620
00:42:51,160 --> 00:42:52,320
I don't get it.

621
00:42:52,400 --> 00:42:55,080
Gosh! You idiot!

622
00:42:55,720 --> 00:43:00,320
How about this? You're on a ship

623
00:43:00,400 --> 00:43:01,920
that is sinking.

624
00:43:02,000 --> 00:43:06,000
You can either
jump off the ship to end it quickly,

625
00:43:06,080 --> 00:43:08,720
or slowly go down with it,

626
00:43:08,840 --> 00:43:10,200
like Jack and Rose in "Titanic."

627
00:43:10,280 --> 00:43:11,560
What will you choose?

628
00:43:12,040 --> 00:43:14,960
But I'm on land.

629
00:43:15,040 --> 00:43:18,760
Yes, you are. You bastard!

630
00:43:19,880 --> 00:43:22,320
You never take anything seriously.
I'm leaving.

631
00:43:25,680 --> 00:43:26,880
Duang.

632
00:43:27,880 --> 00:43:29,800
- Take me home.
- No.

633
00:43:29,880 --> 00:43:31,400
Whatever.

634
00:43:32,440 --> 00:43:36,120
Damn it. Why would I be drowning though?

635
00:43:38,640 --> 00:43:40,640
Damn it! He never listens!

636
00:43:40,720 --> 00:43:42,600
Staying on land is already safe.

637
00:43:43,080 --> 00:43:45,680
Don't pretend we're amphibians.

638
00:43:46,960 --> 00:43:49,680
Your words were so confusing,
stupid warrior.

639
00:43:52,920 --> 00:43:54,120
QIN_
CALLING

640
00:43:55,800 --> 00:43:57,120
Speaker on!

641
00:44:09,920 --> 00:44:11,480
PODDUANG IS CALLING YOU

642
00:44:24,640 --> 00:44:25,840
Hey!

643
00:44:27,080 --> 00:44:28,080
Why are you calling me?

644
00:44:28,640 --> 00:44:30,480
I've made it back to my place.

645
00:44:31,640 --> 00:44:34,080
<i>- That's it?</i>
- There's more.

646
00:44:35,280 --> 00:44:37,160
I hope you have sweet dreams.

647
00:44:37,240 --> 00:44:39,080
I'm going to dream of you tonight.

648
00:44:39,160 --> 00:44:41,440
QIN_ ENDED THE CALL

649
00:44:44,400 --> 00:44:47,720
The ship isn't sinking anymore.

650
00:44:49,280 --> 00:44:52,360
<i>I'll block you if you bother me again.</i>

651
00:44:54,280 --> 00:44:55,200
It's sunk.

652
00:44:55,720 --> 00:44:58,240
But that's okay. I know how to swim!

653
00:45:53,280 --> 00:45:54,440
Excuse me.

654
00:46:07,280 --> 00:46:08,520
It's you!

655
00:46:18,080 --> 00:46:19,080
You're into photography?

656
00:46:23,920 --> 00:46:25,080
What's wrong?

657
00:46:26,720 --> 00:46:29,080
Yes, I am. And so are you?

658
00:46:32,560 --> 00:46:34,080
I never knew that.

659
00:46:37,360 --> 00:46:40,920
That produces a warm tone.
I've shot a roll of it.

660
00:46:47,560 --> 00:46:49,040
That hurt!

661
00:46:51,640 --> 00:46:53,400
So this isn't a dream after all.

662
00:46:53,480 --> 00:46:55,440
I'll ignore you if you keep being silly.

663
00:46:55,520 --> 00:46:57,760
Okay. I won't do it again.

664
00:46:57,840 --> 00:46:59,120
I'm so sorry.

665
00:47:06,400 --> 00:47:07,720
And you're here by yourself?

666
00:47:08,640 --> 00:47:09,880
Do you see anybody else?

667
00:47:11,400 --> 00:47:13,440
If not, that means I'm here by myself.

668
00:47:15,520 --> 00:47:17,040
I also came here all by myself!

669
00:47:20,480 --> 00:47:21,800
Should we get something to eat?

670
00:47:37,360 --> 00:47:40,200
I'll take it as a yes
if you don't say anything.

671
00:47:42,080 --> 00:47:44,760
The film… It produces a warm tone.

672
00:47:45,600 --> 00:47:46,440
A warm tone…

673
00:47:53,440 --> 00:47:55,080
Can I stop you from doing that though?

674
00:48:01,080 --> 00:48:03,800
Stop acting weird or stay here.

675
00:48:04,680 --> 00:48:06,120
I didn't do anything!

676
00:49:57,960 --> 00:49:58,920
What do you wanna eat?

677
00:50:00,640 --> 00:50:03,440
- Ramen will do.
- Let's go.

678
00:51:07,080 --> 00:51:11,360
I've never been to this place.
Can I copy your order?

679
00:51:12,320 --> 00:51:14,080
Stop with that voice.

680
00:51:14,640 --> 00:51:17,520
It can't be done.

681
00:51:34,720 --> 00:51:36,560
Finished? I'll give it to them.

682
00:51:38,200 --> 00:51:40,160
You're taking care of me?

683
00:51:42,080 --> 00:51:43,600
Do it yourself then, damn it.

684
00:51:53,240 --> 00:51:54,440
Do you want me to do it?

685
00:52:00,880 --> 00:52:03,320
You do care about me.

686
00:52:06,040 --> 00:52:08,080
Thank you.

687
00:53:19,680 --> 00:53:21,480
Enjoy.

688
00:53:30,040 --> 00:53:32,480
You looked really adorable
slurping your noodles.

689
00:53:33,880 --> 00:53:35,320
When will you stop with that?

690
00:53:35,400 --> 00:53:37,160
It's because I'm into you.

691
00:53:38,560 --> 00:53:40,320
- I'm heading home.
- Wait up.

692
00:53:41,800 --> 00:53:44,200
- I need some advice.
- What is it?

693
00:53:44,280 --> 00:53:47,320
I'm serious about my singing.

694
00:53:47,800 --> 00:53:49,960
I can't sing, and I don't know what to do.

695
00:53:52,000 --> 00:53:53,600
I don't want to burden you.

696
00:53:54,160 --> 00:53:56,080
Do you have any advice?

697
00:54:00,280 --> 00:54:02,240
Do you want to
practice singing at my place?

698
00:54:05,640 --> 00:54:07,560
You invited me to your place?

699
00:54:47,760 --> 00:54:49,680
<i>As we walk…</i>

700
00:54:49,760 --> 00:54:52,560
Would it be okay
if I spent the night here?

701
00:54:53,080 --> 00:54:54,240
No.

702
00:54:54,880 --> 00:54:57,000
Hey! Are you tired? I bought you a drink.

703
00:54:57,080 --> 00:55:00,320
So, Qin, what do you think of Duang?

704
00:55:02,160 --> 00:55:03,280
<i>Duang's nice, you know?</i>

705
00:55:03,360 --> 00:55:04,640
<i>He cares not only about you,</i>

706
00:55:04,720 --> 00:55:05,640
but also about us.

707
00:55:05,720 --> 00:55:07,120
People try hard to impress.

708
00:55:07,200 --> 00:55:08,800
I like to take my time.

709
00:55:08,880 --> 00:55:10,400
Taking it too long can be bad.

710
00:55:11,600 --> 00:55:12,920
I'm worried about Qin.

711
00:55:13,000 --> 00:55:14,680
I'm worried he'd choose that person.
